        rationale: "All diabetic patients age 40-75 should receive at LEAST moderate-intensity statin therapy. When the calculated 10-year ASCVD risk is >=7.5% (this patient's is 12%), guidelines recommend upgrading to HIGH-intensity statin therapy. Additionally, the presence of diabetes-specific risk enhancers (long duration, neuropathy, retinopathy, albuminuria, ABI <0.9) further supports high-intensity statin."
