        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Untreated hypothyroidism is a correctable risk factor for statin-associated muscle symptoms. The CK is only mildly elevated (<2x ULN), and hypothyroidism alone can cause myalgias and elevated CK. The correct approach is to treat the hypothyroidism first and reassess muscle symptoms after TSH normalizes (6-8 weeks). Many cases of 'statin intolerance' resolve when underlying hypothyroidism or vitamin D deficiency is corrected."
